Program: Outlook
Title: The Race to Rescue Stranded Whales
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p04sqnwk
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 21 Feb 2017
On 10 February 2017, hundreds of pilot whales were stranded on a beach in New Zealand. Outlook's Candida Beveridge went to speak to people on the frontline of the mission to save them. John Di Domenico is an actor who has spent the last 12 years impersonating President Donald Trump. He describes how the recent US presidential election changed his life. (Photo: Volunteer caring for a pilot whale during a mass stranding at Farewell Spit, New Zealand. Credit: Marty Melville/AFP/Getty Images) Show less